Privacy Policy for Uncrypt Effective Date: \[5/24/25\]

1. Introduction

Uncrypt \(“we”, “us”, or “our”\) is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you use the Uncrypt mobile application \(“App”\). 

2. Information We Collect

a. No Personal Information Required

● Uncrypt does not require you to create an account or provide your email address or any personal information to use the app. 

b. Decryption Logs and Device Information

● When you attempt to decrypt a code, the following information may be collected and securely logged:

● The code you entered \(for audit/security purposes\)

● The result of the decryption \(success or failure\)

● Timestamp of the attempt

● Device information \(such as device model, operating system version, and anonymized device identifier\)

● \(Optional\) Geolocation data, if you grant permission c. Usage Data

● We may collect anonymous usage statistics to improve app performance and user experience. 

3. How We Use Your Information

● To provide and improve the decryption service

● To ensure the security and integrity of the app

● For audit and troubleshooting purposes

● To comply with legal obligations

4. Data Sharing and Disclosure

● We do not sell, trade, 

or rent your personal information to third parties. 

● Decryption logs and device information are stored securely and are only accessible to authorized personnel for security and audit purposes. 

● We may disclose information if required by law or to protect our rights and users’ safety. 

5. Data Security

● We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your data. 

● All logs and device information are stored securely and transmitted over encrypted connections. 

6. Children’s Privacy

● Uncrypt is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. 

7. Your Choices

● You may choose not to use the app if you do not agree with this policy. 

● You can request deletion of your logged data by contacting us at 

\[info@ilighttech.com\]. 

8. Changes to This Privacy Policy

● We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated effective date. 

9. Contact Us

If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or your data, please contact us at:

Email: \[information@ilighttech.com\]

Company: iLight Tech



